Fognini, aiming to win a fifth title, will now lock horns with Nadal's compatriot David Ferrer in Sunday's final.

Second seed Ferrer came through a comfortable last-four clash against Austrian Andreas Haider-Maurer 7-5 6-1 to secure his spot in Sunday's showpiece.

The women's final will be contested by top seed Sara Errani and rising star Anna Schmiedlova after they won their respective semis on Saturday.

Errani, who has only dropped one set in Brazil this week, needed just under 90 minutes to squeeze past Sweden's Johanna Larsson 7-5 6-3.

The Italian, who had not dropped a set in five previous meetings with Larsson, was in trouble 3-0 down in the second set, but she reeled off six games in a row to claim the win.

