'I think I was just a little bit more consistent and a little bit more aggressive today,' Errani told the WTA website. 'It was a much different match than the one I played yesterday - but I was still fighting for every point and trying my best, and I'm glad I could make it through to the final here in Rio.'

Slovakian Schmiedlova, 20, upset second seed Irina-Camelia Begu 6-3, 4-6, 6-2 after two hours and 43 minutes to secure her place in the final.

'I was playing well in the first set. The second set was tough, but I'm glad I was able to start playing better again in the third set and win the match,' she said.

 

